(78, NULL, NULL, '231', 729.000, 1, 14, 0.00, NULL, NULL, '2016-03-02 10:25:53', 9, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 11, NULL, 0, 37, 0, 17, 0, NULL, NULL, 'Sony Full HD Handy Camcorder HDR-CX220/S (8.9 Megapixel, Silver)', '<p style="margin: 0px 0px 20px; max-width: 770px; font-family: ''Proxima Nova'', Proxima-Nova, proxima-nova, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 17px; line-height: 23.8px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">Sony&#39;s been building its A7 series of Alpha full-frame mirrorless cameras, each model has made compromises: great sensitivity but low resolution (&nbsp;<span class="link" section="shortcodeLink" style="display: inline-block;"><a href="http://www.cnet.com/products/sony-a7s-ii/" style="transition-property: all; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: ease; text-decoration: none; cursor: pointer; color: rgb(184, 0, 0); font-weight: 600;">A7S II</a></span>&nbsp;), sharp image quality but slow autofocus system (&nbsp;<span class="link" section="shortcodeLink" style="display: inline-block;"><a href="http://www.cnet.com/products/sony-alpha-ilce-7r-body-only/" style="transition-property: all; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: ease; text-decoration: none; cursor: pointer; color: rgb(184, 0, 0); font-weight: 600;">A7R</a></span>&nbsp;), fast autofocus system but not best-in-the-line photo quality (&nbsp;<span class="link" section="shortcodeLink" style="display: inline-block;"><a href="http://www.cnet.com/products/sony-a7-ii/" style="transition-property: all; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: ease; text-decoration: none; cursor: pointer; color: rgb(184, 0, 0); font-weight: 600;">A7 II</a></span>&nbsp;). But with its latest entry, the A7R II, Sony tosses all its newest technology at it.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 20px; max-width: 770px; font-family: ''Proxima Nova'', Proxima-Nova, proxima-nova, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 17px; line-height: 23.8px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">In the newly reignited war over resolution in pro cameras, Sony&#39;s A7R II slips in at 42 megapixels, right between the&nbsp;<span class="link" section="shortcodeLink" style="display: inline-block;"><a href="http://www.cnet.com/products/canon-eos-5ds-r/" style="transition-property: all; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: ease; text-decoration: none; cursor: pointer; color: rgb(184, 0, 0); font-weight: 600;">Canon 5DS R</a></span>&nbsp;&#39;s 50MP and the&nbsp;<span class="link" section="shortcodeLink" style="display: inline-block;"><a href="http://www.cnet.com/products/nikon-d810/" style="transition-property: all; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: ease; text-decoration: none; cursor: pointer; color: rgb(184, 0, 0); font-weight: 600;">Nikon D810</a></span>&nbsp;&#39;s 36MP. But the camera doesn&#39;t really need to claim highest resolution to stand out in the crowd of full-frame cameras; its excellent photo quality, great video (including support for 4K) and compact, comfortable design speak for themselves.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 20px; max-width: 770px; font-family: ''Proxima Nova'', Proxima-Nova, proxima-nova, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 17px; line-height: 23.8px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">The camera costs $3,200, &pound;2,800 or AU$4,500. That&#39;s not cheap, and while it&#39;s less expensive than the 5DS R ($3,900, &pound;3,200, AU$5,540), it&#39;s more expensive than the D810 ($3,000, &pound;2,380, AU$4,000). What the money buys you, though, is an excellent and compact full-frame mirrorless camera that&#39;s more suited for shooting video than its dSLR counterparts.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style="text-rendering: optimizeLegibility; margin: 15px 0px 5px; max-width: 100%; zoom: 1; font-size: 32px; line-height: 1.0909em; font-family: ''Proxima Nova'', Proxima-Nova, proxima-nova, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -0.009em; top: 10px; display: inline-block; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">Image quality</h3>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 20px; max-width: 770px; font-family: ''Proxima Nova'', Proxima-Nova, proxima-nova, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 17px; line-height: 23.8px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">This camera incorporates the first a full-frame&nbsp;<a data-component="externalLink" href="http://www.adorama.com/alc/0012961/article/FAQ-Whats-a-Backside-Illuminated-Sensor" style="transition-property: all; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: ease; text-decoration: none; cursor: pointer; color: rgb(184, 0, 0); font-weight: 600;" target="_blank">BSI</a>&nbsp;(backside illuminated) CMOS sensor (Sony&#39;s Exmor R branded sensors). BSI sensors have become extremely popular because their construction makes them more sensitive in low light than traditional CMOS imagers and because their structure allows for faster the readout speeds needed to support high-frame-rate video and stills.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class="shortcode gallery size_small" data-component="[" section="shortcodeGallery" style="position: relative; margin-top: 30px; margin-bottom: 30px; z-index: 0; clear: both; max-width: 100%; font-family: ''Proxima Nova'', Proxima-Nova, proxima-nova, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 17px; line-height: 23.8px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">\r\n<h6 style="text-rendering: optimizeLegibility; margin: 10px 0px 25px; color: rgb(184, 0, 0); text-transform: uppercase; font-size: 0.824em; height: 3px; line-height: 5px; max-width: none; background-color: rgb(228, 231, 234);"><a data-component="imageGalleryModal" data-image-gallery-modal-options="{" href="http://www.cnet.com/pictures/sony-a7r-ii-full-resolution-photo-samples/" style="transition-property: all; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: ease; text-decoration: none; cursor: pointer; color: rgb(184, 0, 0);"><span style="padding: 0px 10px 0px 0px; display: inline-block; height: 9px; max-width: 524px; word-wrap